## 13. Thirteen conversion-killing mistakes and their fixes

**Mistake 1: Burying the hook.** Spending 60+ seconds on introductions before stating value. Fix: lead with a bold promise or pattern interrupt within 5 seconds. ❌ "Hey everyone, my name is John and I'm the founder of…" ✅ "If you're a supplement brand doing $500K+ per year, I can show you the exact email system generating an extra $50–150K annually for brands like yours."

**Mistake 2: Vague, generic language.** "We help eCom brands make more money with email." Fix: hyper-specificity. ✅ "We help supplement brands doing $50K–$500K/month add $8–15K in monthly revenue through abandoned cart, post-purchase, and win-back sequences."

**Mistake 3: Talking about yourself instead of the prospect.** The first 70% should be about THEM. Fix: use the 80/20 rule — 80% prospect-focused. Weave credentials into their story, not separate from it.

**Mistake 4: No unique mechanism.** Without one, you're just another agency making identical claims. Fix: name your proprietary framework and explain WHY results happen differently with your approach.

**Mistake 5: Weak or absent social proof.** Video testimonials are perceived as **76% more trustworthy** than text reviews. Fix: 2–3 specific case studies with before/after numbers, timeframes, and client names.

**Mistake 6: No value delivery before the close.** Going 10+ minutes without a single insight, proof point, or useful takeaway. Fix: drop a proof point or insight every 2–3 minutes. Use open loops to maintain curiosity.

**Mistake 7: Too logical, no emotional engagement.** Listing features and data without connecting to feelings. Fix: paint pain vividly, use future pacing, tell transformation stories. Emotionally connected prospects are **3.2x more likely** to buy.

**Mistake 8: Unclear CTA or decision paralysis.** One clear CTA repeated throughout. Walk them through exact steps: "Click the button below, choose a time, fill out 3 quick questions. Takes 60 seconds."

**Mistake 9: No urgency or reason to act now.** Fix: real capacity scarcity, seasonal relevance, opportunity cost framing. Never manufacture fake deadlines.

**Mistake 10: Poor audio quality.** This destroys credibility faster than any other production issue. Fix: $150 USB microphone, quiet room, no echo.

**Mistake 11: Ignoring objections.** Unaddressed doubts fester and kill conversions silently. Fix: list the top 5 objections from your sales calls, address each directly. For email agencies, the biggest is always "I've been burned by agencies before."

**Mistake 12: Feature dumping.** "We set up 12 automated email flows" means nothing without "which means." Fix: for every feature, add "which means [benefit] so that [emotional outcome]."

**Mistake 13: Autoplay inflating metrics.** If your play rate seems unusually high (70%+) but sales are weak, autoplay may be hiding the truth. Fix: turn off autoplay, measure true play rate. Below 55% true play rate means your landing page isn't compelling enough to make people press play.

