## The bottom line on what actually converts in 2026

Every framework analyzed — Conversionly, Brunson, Suby, Georgi, Brown, Benson, Gordon — converges on the same truth: **the offer and the mechanism matter more than the script structure, and the script matters more than the production.** A VSL filmed on an iPhone with a $150 mic and a genuinely differentiated mechanism will outperform a $10,000 production with generic "we write great emails" positioning every single time. The template above gives you the architecture. Your mechanism, your proof, and your ability to articulate your prospect's pain better than they can — those are the variables that determine whether your VSL prints money or gathers dust. Start with RMBC Phase 1: research your prospect's exact words, exact frustrations, and exact failed solutions. Build the mechanism second. Write the script third. Film it last. And never stop testing.